<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 2:41PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Gray and central
Roberts Counties through 315 PM CDT...
At 240 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles northwest of Codman to 6 miles west of
Lefors to 10 miles south of Kingsmill. Movement was northeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Lefors, Kingsmill, Lake Mcclellan and Codman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
